Set Up a Streaming Data Transform

When you set up a streaming data transform, it reads and processes all records in the source data lake object (DLO) and writes the data to the target object. The source and target objects must be different objects.

Create a target DLO.
Multiple streaming data transforms can use the same DLO as a target. However, you can’t use a DLO that is being used by a data stream as a target.
On the Data Lake Objects tab, click New.
Decide whether to use an existing DLO as a template or create a new one.
Enter a name and API name.
You can’t change these names after the object is created.
Select the appropriate category for the data in this DLO.
Category selection affects billing and DMO mapping. You can’t change the DLO’s category after it’s created.Learn more about categories in Salesforce Help.
Review the DLO’s status. When the status is Active, you can add it to a streaming data transform.
Create the streaming data transform.
On the Data Transforms tab, click New.

If your org has already used the maximum number of transforms allowed, the New button doesn’t appear.

Complete the required fields.
In the Expression field, enter a SQL statement to tell the streaming data transform which records to process and how to map the transformed output to the target DLO.
Verify your SQL statement’s syntax by clicking Check Syntax.
If a streaming data transform contains syntax errors or validation errors, such as incorrect API names for the source DLO and target DLOs, you can’t save it. These errors appear on the left side. Fix them before saving.
Save the transformation. Streaming data transforms are activated immediately when saved.
You can’t change a streaming data transform after saving it. If you must change a streaming data transform, delete it and create another one.
